===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
{{Han compound|垚|兀|ls=ic|ls2=psc|c1=p|c2=s|t1=tall (''of earth'')|t2=towering and bald}}.

The oracle bone script consists of two {{zh-l|*土|soil; earth}} at the top and a kneeling man stylized as {{zh-l|*兀}} at the bottom.

===Etymology===
Compare the second syllable of {{cog|my|အငူ|t=promontory, headland, cape}} ({{zh-ref|Luce, 1981}}).

